Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2530885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pec1665702933838.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pec1665702933838.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pec1665702933838.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pec1665702933838\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Logon Path on iSeries\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49190e1_d49191e1_d49192e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">$DB2 DB2:</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DbmsDirectory</var>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">:</code>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var>} <code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code> {<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>}</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pec1665702933838__li_d23981e1_d23982e1_d23983e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DbmsDirectory</var>—name of the local relational database directory entry \n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pec1665702933838__li_d23984e1_d23985e1_d23986e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>—collection or schema name in which the data resides. This collection or schema is actually a library that must have been created using the <code class=\"ph codeph\">create collection</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">create schema</code> SQL statement. Libraries that were created using other methods do not contain the DB2 catalog table views required by Uniface, and therefore cannot be used.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pec1665702933838__li_d23987e1_d23988e1_d23989e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var> and <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>—user and password for the DB2 database. Optional.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pec1665702933838__section_l4t_kpj_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d120115e112\">Local Relational Database Directory Entry </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49196e1_d49197e1_d49198e1\">You can obtain the name of the local relational\n            database directory entry by using the CL command <code class=\"ph codeph\">WRKRDBDIRE</code>. From the\n            list of entries displayed, use the name of the one that has <code class=\"ph codeph\">*LOCAL</code> as\n            its remote location.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49199e1_d49200e1_d49201e1\">If there is no such entry, you must create one:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"pec1665702933838__ol_mxc_npj_3cc\">\n<li class=\"li\">In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Option</span> field on the top line, specify a\n                  <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">1</kbd>. In the empty <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Entry</span> field to its\n               right, specify a name.<div class=\"p\">\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"pec1665702933838__note_sbq_4pj_3cc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> It is common practice to use the network\n                     name of the iSeries machine or the machine’s serial number.</div>\n</div></li>\n<li class=\"li\">Click <span class=\"ph keypress\">Enter</span>. In the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Name or\n                  address</span> field, enter <kbd class=\"ph userinput\">*LOCAL</kbd>.</li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"pec1665702933838__section_mlc_spj_3cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d120115e162\">Normal and Server Mode on iSeries</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49211e1_d49212e1_d49213e1\">On iSeries, a running Uniface Server job or Uniface\n            batch job always has an implicit connection to the database.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49214e1_d49215e1_d49216e1\">When you omit the <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var> and\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var> in the path, the connector uses this implicit\n            connection. This is called <dfn class=\"term\">Normal mode</dfn> and limits data access to this one\n            connection. The authorities it has for accessing or modifying database objects are those\n            of the user profile under which the job runs.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pec1665702933838__p_d49217e1_d49218e1_d49219e1\">When you specify the <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2UserName</var>\n            and <var class=\"keyword varname\">DB2Password</var>, you instruct the connector to establish an explicit\n            connection using the provided user name and password, instead of using the implicit\n            database connection. This is called <dfn class=\"term\">Server mode</dfn>, and it allows more than\n            one connection to the database. This is required when components are activated with\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">TRANSACTION=TRUE</code> qualifier.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530885\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Logon Path on iSeries Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Logon Path on iSeries $DB2 DB2: { DbmsDirectory } : { Database } | { DB2UserName } | { DB2Password } DbmsDirectory —name of the local relational database directory entry Database —collection or schema name in which the data resides. This collection or schema is actually a library that must have been created using the create collection or create schema SQL statement. Libraries that were created using other methods do not contain the DB2 catalog table views required by Uniface, and therefore cannot be used. DB2UserName and DB2Password —user and password for the DB2 database. Optional. Local Relational Database Directory Entry You can obtain the name of the local relational database directory entry by using the CL command WRKRDBDIRE . From the list of entries displayed, use the name of the one that has *LOCAL as its remote location. If there is no such entry, you must create one: In the Option field on the top line, specify a 1 . In the empty Entry field to its right, specify a name. Note: It is common practice to use the network name of the iSeries machine or the machine’s serial number. Click Enter . In the Name or address field, enter *LOCAL . Normal and Server Mode on iSeries On iSeries, a running Uniface Server job or Uniface batch job always has an implicit connection to the database. When you omit the DB2UserName and DB2Password in the path, the connector uses this implicit connection. This is called Normal mode and limits data access to this one connection. The authorities it has for accessing or modifying database objects are those of the user profile under which the job runs. When you specify the DB2UserName and DB2Password , you instruct the connector to establish an explicit connection using the provided user name and password, instead of using the implicit database connection. This is called Server mode , and it allows more than one connection to the database. This is required when components are activated with TRANSACTION=TRUE qualifier. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}